spanGrp.span: ‘Where there was a small house, there lived a seal.
Mãĩ të mãĩ estee jũ kajki rö yuliski jãrga jeska foka sẽr-gẽ e-gla
Ñerö jie dul jũ jãr sigö
then the phone rang and he answered.
ñerö esteee telefono buranã' ñerö jie të í kontestar-wã
The female mouse called him and he told him “let’s go for a ride”.
Ñerö esteee koño (_) koño estee busi nẽ të í chagá ñerö jie të (_) ñerö í shá-ite „Banãra se shkö esteee ñãyulö“
So he got ready put his hat on, grabbed the keys and left.
Ñerö jie jẽk alistar-wã të sombrero jiáwã jie të estee yabe gugá-wã mẽnẽũ-mĩ
Then he got where the female mouse was at the side waiting for him.
deu-mĩ-ra estee koño yaba esteee busi je dul kö ska të í kikse-gẽ
Off they went; on the road they saw a frog playing with a ball
Ñerö í mẽnẽũ-lo-mĩ mãĩ ñala inga estee sapo dajũ-te estee bola wa je jinõ-gẽ
and their car crashed against a stone,
ñerö mẽnẽũ jie-wa jie-wa mẽnẽũ-lo-mĩ-te estee jak mẽ í í karro pá
turned over, and the frog saw that the seal was dead.
ñerö í í bolká-wã-nãu-mĩ ñerö esteee foka eee (_) sapo të sũã'-ra í döá-wã
He saw how his soul went up in the air but they managed to grab it;
Ñerö sũã-ite-ra í alma mẽnẽũ jui estee (_) esteee siwã' inga Ñerö jie-wa të í gugá-wã
when he saw that the mouse was on a branch and came down,
ñerö esteee mãĩ í sũã'-ite-ra estee koño (_) yaba busi je (_) kal mẽ esteee (_) estee kaljula inga Jeska ñerö jie jawã-te
he/she saw that the seal was dead;
so they called the ambulance and put him in it.
ñerö jie-wa të ambulansia chagá je jãrga í pakká-wã-ite ñerö mẽnẽtse wã
The frog remained there and cried a lot.
Mãĩ sapo je (_) je jatanã-wã jinõ-gẽ köũ
Meanwhile he saw the seal was coming on crutches
ñerö je batamẽra í sũã'-ite-ra foka dajũ (m) pero je dajũ rö muleta inga
and ran fast and brought a bed and put him on it
Ñerö estee mãĩ tunã' bö' të mãĩ jaka bete í wã je inga í mã'wã-ite
put a blanket on the ground and the seal lay down;
Ñerö mãĩ esteee kobija tuláka-ite jiski inga ñerö foka të jẽk mã'wã
the frog fetched food and gave it to him and saw that the seal got well;
Ñerö mãĩ dá-te walí shkö í wã je mã'-ite ĩã ñerö (hm) esteee sũã'-ite-ra foka je estee je böinã'-ka-ra
so he took off the bandage;
the seal stood up and saw that the car was not there,
ñerö foka jẽk döá-ka ñerö ya jie të sũã-ra (extra) ka karro juẽ-nã
so they went to look for it;
Ñerö (_) ká-lu-mĩ í ká-lu-mĩ (_) estee (_) estee ñala inga
then they stopped and saw that the female mouse was driving the car, which was already fixed.
ñerö jẽk döachá ñerö jie-wa të sũã'-ra (_) estee koño yaba je wa estee karro datsẽ' ñera karro böi-nã'-wã
So they all, the mouse, the seal and the frog, went for a ride.
ñera/ ñerö esteee í karro inga (_) jie-wa mẽnẽũ-lo-mĩ estee pasear-wã koño jamẽ esteee foka estee sapo je mẽnẽũ-lo-mĩ pasear-wã
The female drove the car; it was ok again.’
Ñera estee ko este koño este karro mẽnẽtsẽ' böinã'-ka-nẽ estabaglö
